methods.safelyParseFrom:
Converts an InputStream to a BarrageMessage in the context of the provided parameters.

:param options: (io.deephaven.extensions.barrage.util.StreamReaderOptions) - the options related to parsing this message
:param expectedColumns: (java.util.BitSet) - the columns expected to appear in the stream, null implies all columns
:param columnChunkTypes: (io.deephaven.chunk.ChunkType[]) - the types to use for each column chunk
:param columnTypes: (java.lang.Class<?>[]) - the actual type for the column
:param componentTypes: (java.lang.Class<?>[]) - the actual component type for the column
:param stream: (java.io.InputStream) - the input stream that holds the message to be parsed
:return: (io.deephaven.engine.table.impl.util.BarrageMessage) a BarrageMessage filled out by the stream's payload
